# Add Connector App UI

> **Status: stub — implementation pending.** Contract only. Targets the
> working tree of whichever repo owns the `app_ui` component.

## Purpose

Build the interactive app UI a customer uses to configure the connector:
the profile-creation flow — an OAuth "connect" button (bound to
`/add-connector-oauth`'s authorize route) or credential input fields — and
the quick-settings form, rendered from the settings-form contract
`/define-connector-interface` defines so the form and the backend codecs
stay in lockstep.

The app UI is part of the connector's surface, with two possible homes
(the `app_ui` note in `/scaffold-connector`'s connector-anatomy
reference): a frontend-role repo in the scaffold target's `repos` list,
built in that repo's idiom, or — when the target has no frontend repo,
as in greenfield mode — the ui unit the connector serves itself (for
cloudflare-workers, a React single-page app built with Vite and served
as static assets by the same Worker).

Phase: **frontend**.

## Inputs (from connector-spec.yaml)

- `auth.model` → OAuth connect button vs credential fields; `redirect_uri`.
- `quick_settings[]` (`type`, `fields[]` with name/type/required/purpose) →
  the form.
- `identifier_groups[]` → what the profile advertises.

## Outputs

- The connector's profile-creation and quick-settings forms: React
  components in the frontend repo, or the connector-served SPA's
  components in greenfield mode.

## Human gates

- Local UI code only — shipped through the owning repo's normal PR
  review; no direct deploy from this skill.

